<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,223,500]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,368,392]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[324,584,368,392]" class="Chilopoda" family="Scolopendridae" genus="Otostigmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavalcantii">
<emphasis box="[324,584,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Otostigmus cavalcantii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the subgenus 
<emphasis box="[871,1052,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Dactylotergitius</emphasis>
and was recently revised by Chagas-Jr 
<emphasis box="[224,280,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[294,356,404,428]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="2007.0">2007</number>
). It is widely distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[660,731,404,428]" name="Brazil" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, but there are also records from 
<collectingCountry box="[1088,1203,404,428]" name="Argentina" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. The male of 
<taxonomicName class="Chilopoda" family="Scolopendridae" genus="Otostigmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavalcantii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<collectingCountry box="[1354,1377,405,428]" name="Iceland" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">O</collectingCountry>
. cavalcantii
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents a digitiform appendix at the posterior border of the tergite 
<number box="[1028,1056,439,463]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="21.0">21</number>
as in 
<taxonomicName box="[1131,1268,440,464]" class="Chilopoda" family="Scolopendridae" genus="Otostigmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scolopendromorpha" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudatus">
<emphasis box="[1131,1268,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<collectingCountry box="[1131,1154,440,463]" name="Iceland" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">O</collectingCountry>
. caudatus
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs in the presence of a pointed sclerotized coxopleural process (
<bibRefCitation author="Bucherl" box="[912,1088,476,500]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refString="Bucherl, W. (1939 a) Tres scolopendrideos novos. Revista de Biologia e Hygiene, 10 (1), 54 - 64." type="journal article" year="1939" yearSuffix="a">
Bücherl, 
<number box="[1016,1075,476,500]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="1939.0">1939</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
; Chagas-Jr 
<emphasis box="[1219,1275,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[1289,1350,476,500]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="2007.0">2007</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
